\">Credit Card Expiration Date:</label>\n        <input type=\"text\" id=\"credit_card_expiration\" name=\"credit_card_expiration\" placeholder=\"MM/YY\" pattern=\"[0-9]{2}/[0-9]{2}\" title=\"MM/YY credit card expiration date\"><br><br>\n\n        <!-- Credit Card CVV Input Field (Secure Example) -->\n        <label for=\"credit_card_cvv\">Credit Card CVV:</label>\n        <input type=\"text\" id=\"credit_card_cvv\" name=\"credit_card_cvv\" placeholder=\"CVV\" pattern=\"[0-9]{3}\" title=\"3-digit credit card CVV\"><br><br>\n\n        <!-- Submit Button -->\n        <input type=\"submit\" value=\"Submit\">\n    </form>\n</body>\n</html>\n```\n\nIn this revised form, we've added a field for social security numbers, along with a pattern attribute to ensure the input is in the correct format (XXX-XX-XXXX). We've also included best practices for secure form design, such as:\n\n*   Using a secure input type (`<input type=\"text\">`) for sensitive data like social security numbers.\n*   Using a pattern attribute to enforce a specific input format.\n*   Using a title attribute to provide a hint to the user about the expected input format.\n*   Using the `autocomplete` attribute to prevent browsers from auto-filling sensitive fields.\n\nAdditionally, you can use the `readonly` attribute to prevent users from editing sensitive fields, and the `disabled` attribute to prevent users from submitting the form until all required fields are filled.\n\n```html\n<input type=\"text\" id=\"social_security_number\" name=\"social_security_number\" placeholder=\"XXX-XX-XXXX\" pattern=\"[0-9]{3}-[0-9]{2}-[0-9]{4}\" title=\"XXX-XX-XXXX social security number\" readonly>\n```\n\nThis will prevent users from editing the social security number field, ensuring that the sensitive data is not compromised.\n\n```html\n<input type=\"submit\" value=\"Submit\" disabled>\n```\n\nThis will prevent the form from being submitted until all required fields are filled, ensuring that sensitive data is not submitted until it is complete and accurate.",
